f=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerfrm32.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=398.topic&index=4>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> <img src="http://www.ezboard.com/images/posticons/pi_question_mark.gif" align=absmiddle>  Re: Mage vs Beastlord</span><hr size=1> Work on not getting aggroed so badly that your pet can't get the mob off you.<br>
<br>
The best way to do that is to suck it up and not use an earth pet at low levels so that you don't grow dependent on the root.  It's very easy to gain a lot of aggro while a mob is rooted and then get screwed when the root breaks and your pet can't taunt the mob off you.<br>
<br>
When you do gain aggro, don't run away from your pet.  He's your bestest buddy and will fight to the death for you, but if you run away from him, the poor little guy just can't keep up to help you out.  The fact that the pet will stop to cast spells will just get him farther behind you.<br>
<br>
Instead, run back *through* your pet.  Do this a few times.  Take a couple of hits and keep training the mob back through the pet.  Eventually the pet will regain aggro. <p></p><i>Edited by: <A HREF=http://pub102.ezboard.com/bthemagicianstower.showUserPublicProfile?gid=ithryn>Ithryn</A> at: 11/6/02 5:55:30 pm<br></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#989dca><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub102.ezboard.com/bthemagicianstower.showUserPublicProfile?gid=asegai>Asegai</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Magician</span><br>  Posts: 4<br> <font color=#333333>(11/6/02 7:29:09 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerfrm32.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=398.topic&index=5>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> <img src="http://www.ezboard.com/images/posticons/pi_question_mark.gif" align=absmiddle>  Let me clarify</span><hr size=1> My deaths have come from adds, not the mobs I'm fighting.  I feel so vulnerable because I need my pet to tank.  If I had a permanent SoW, I would be unstoppalbe or even root.(Guess that's why we don't hvae them.  Is there anything that can help us get away if something is on us and pet is almost dead from the first mob?<br>
<br>
What about the quest for the spirit bridle in Befallen that I heard about around lvl 12.  Is that a good one for mages?  Are there any quests or spells that I can look forward to as a mage that are 'defining'?<br>
<br>
Finally, does nuking get boring at later levels or is a mage still challenging in the 30'and 40s?<br>
