<br>
Also, TANK for your pet at lower levels. DS yourself, and TANK. At high levels you cant anymore so raise your Defensive skills at lower levels. You will need them.<br>
<br>
Finally, the adds. First you have to figure out how much life your pet has left. If you think hes got enough hp's to servive tanking 2 pets while you nuke one to death, pull the second through the pet and the first mob. You may have to do this once or twice. Eventually you will get both to stick. Then, if you think pet can survive, start nuking. If not, gate or run to zone. :P<br>
<br>
At higher levels you will chain pets to tank adds, but thats a totally different ball of wax :P<br>
<br>
Iumenate, Arch-Mage, Sol Ro <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#dcdeed><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub102.ezboard.com/bthemagicianstower.showUserPublicProfile?gid=marlborodc>MarlboroDC</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Elementalist</span><br>  Posts: 141<br> <font color=#333333>(11/6/02 7:57:34 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerfrm32.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=398.topic&index=8>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> <img src="http://www.ezboard.com/images/posticons/pi_question_mark.gif" align=absmiddle>  Re: Let me clarify</span><hr size=1> As you play a mage more you learn to pick your targets better so you don't get adds.  Though I'm taking it your new to the game which means your just lacking the experience so best advice is just go out there and kick some butt while having fun and the knowledge and confidence will flow in soon enough.<br>
<br>
As for gear I was the true noob with two 3int ear rings and raw silk and I lvled up np gear is only so/so even today but the class isn't as gear dependent as others so just looking around the net and see if ya find anything you like.<br>
<br>
As for nuking I honestly never touched a nuke except in a crunch solo after about lvl 30 till PoP I never needed to honestly but I'm not a nuke mage I'm a pet mage.<br>
<br>
As for the payoff I think it's worth it.  Playing one of the most unique classes in the game is fun and has been a challenge I've have bad days like everyone else but when ya get going you really get going.<br>
<br>
Mulkosaur Rex lvl 59 Magician Brell Serilis   <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#989dca><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub102.ezboard.com/bthemagicianstower.showUserPublicProfile?gid=kinelaria>Kinelaria</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Master Summoner</span><br>  Posts: 454<br> <font color=#333333>(11/7/02 4:56:55 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerfrm32.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=398.topic&index=9>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> <img src="http://www.ezboard.com/images/posticons/pi_question_mark.gif" align=absmiddle>  Re: Let me clarify</span><hr size=1> I stopped having problems with adds when they removed the delay between pet commands. Well, adds are still a problem, just it's easier to escape them now, and if it's only 2, maybe 3 mobs I might even beat them if they're not too strong.<br>
<br>
I use a hotkey like this for using /pet kill:<br>
<br>
Line #1&gt; /pet back off<br>
Line #2&gt; /pet kill<br>
<br>
If I get an add, I switch target to the add, move close to my pet, and hit my pet attack key. Pet will switch targets 99% of the time, and if I am lucky, roots it right off the bat and I can move away safely. Usually this buys me time to at least run or gate, but sometimes I can manage to kill the mobs using heals and burning down one mob quickly.<br>
<br>
It's true that magicians don't really have much defense outside their pets. But it's part of being able to deal out so much raw offensive power.<br>
<br>
Kinelaria<br>
Taeru<br>
Lana<br>
